John Y. Televantos Ph.D.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 3:59 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Arsenal Capital Partners



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
John Y. Televantos Ph.D.Partner and Co-Head of the Specialty Industrials Group, Arsenal Capital PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships64--
Background

		Dr. John Y. Televantos, Ph.D., is a Partner and Co-Head of the Specialty Industrials Group at Arsenal Capital Partners. He joined the firm on January 2006 as Executive Vice President. His area of focus is portfolio management and specialty industrials. Previously, Dr. Televantos served as a Vice President of Hercules Inc. since April 2002 and as the President of Aqualon Company since April 2002. He served as the President, Chief Executive Officer and Chief Operating ... Officer at Foamex International from June 1999 to December 2001. Dr. Televantos also served as the President and Founder of Helios Chemical Company and as the Vice President of Development Businesses and Research at Lyondell Chemical Company since 1998. He held various executive positions in the chemical industry in the last 20 years. His early career was concentrated in research and development at Union Carbide as a Director of Research and Development of Specialty Chemicals and Arco Chemical Co. as a Vice President of Strategy and Commercial Development. He has been Lead Director at Balchem Corp. since August 2010. Dr. Televantos has been a Director of Balchem Corp. since February 21, 2005. He is a Co-Chairman at Doing a World of Good" campaign. He serves on the Boards of Acella Performance Materials, Interdynamics Inc., Dash Multi-Corp, Flowchem, Kel-Tech, International Fiber Corporation, Inhance Technologies, IGM Specialties Holding, Chromaflo Technologies, Fluoro-Seal Holdings and LuriteK. Dr. Televantos served on the boards of Novolyte, Source Refrigeration & HVA, Reilly Industries, Vertellus Specialties, Velsicol Chemical Corp., Genovique Specialties, IDQ Holdings. He was a Director of Royal Adhesives & Sealants, LLC  since December 15, 2010. Additionally, he sat on several public and private company Boards and is affiliated with other key industry- related groups. Dr. Televantos received a Ph.D. and B.S both in Chemical Engineering, from University of London, United Kingdom.Read Full Background




